This paper deals with text mining and supervised learning algorithms for term extraction, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), which are covered by cs.CL and cs.IR. The use of statistical criteria measures and evolutionary learning algorithms also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL). Overall, cs.CL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.DL.
